50 year old male with no significant past medical history, on adderal and testosterone only but family history of paternal MI in 50s, complains of 15 min of 7/10 sudden mid upper back pain radiating to chest and jaw, with diaphoresis and dyspnea. no dvt symptoms and no PE risk factors. on arrival to ER, vitals normal, appeared clammy with pale and diaphoretic skin, systolic blood pressure 128 on right, and 145 on left, EKG showed inferior wall STEMI. pt given ASA 325mg on arrival, then 500ml of Normal saline, then 0.4mg SL nitro, another 500ml of saline then another 0.4mg SL nitro 5 minutes later since pain stayed in the 6-7 range. EMS was called as soon as EKG was completed and read as STEMI. see nursing chart for exact times. medics reported that they will take patient to nearest cath lab capable hospital- we are a freestanding ER- therefore I called the charge nurse there to inform them they are coming.